Police officers on leave or deployed elsewhere in SA are now being recalled to urgently help with the widespread protests across the country. Members of the Police and Prisons Civil Rights Union are being urged to be vigilant and exercise extreme caution. eNCA's Clement Manyathela speaks to Popcru Spokesperson Richard Mamabolo. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Several people dead, dozens arrested and damage of millions of rand. Large parts of Gauteng and KwaZulu Natal resemble a warzone following waves of looting sprees since the weekend. President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to speak on Monday night about the violence. WATCH: Looters ransack Jabulani Mall The army has also been deployed to hotspots. Now police officers on leave or deployed elsewhere in the country are also being recalled to urgently help with the widespread protests across the country. The Police and Prisons Civil Rights Union is urging its members to be vigilant and exercise extreme caution.